Browse

Calculations for percent browse per species and average heights of browsed versus unbrowsed woody species assume that the inside subplots were not browsed. Thus, all browse data uses only the outside subplots in each treatment zone.

The plot below compares the average height of the only three species that occurred inside all three treatment zones.

These figures plot the average heights of species that occur both inside and outside a treatment zone for each individual treatment. The plots compare the average heights of the woody individuals inside and outside, browsed and unbrowsed.

In the Control plot, there were no recorded browsed individuals of Virginia Creeper.

In the Two-Sided Release plot, there was one recorded browsed Rosa Multiflora individual, but its height was not measured. The plot does not reflect how that individuals average height was recorded as NA.
